            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cream and mix",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Preheat the oven to 175 degrees C (conventional). Grease and line a 900 g loaf tin. Beat the butter and sugar together with an electric mixer for at least 5 minutes, until the mixture is pale and has increased noticeably in volume. Add the eggs one at a time, beating for 30 seconds after each. Add the vanilla. If the mixture begins to look curdled, add a tablespoon of the measured flour to bring it back. Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt, then fold into the batter in two additions, mixing only until the flour has just disappeared.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Bake and cool",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pour the batter into the prepared tin and smooth the top. Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean and the top is deep golden with a pronounced crack down the middle. The crack is normal and desirable. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack. Leave for at least 20 minutes before slicing; it cuts much more cleanly once cool.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": null,
